        <mxCell id="legend" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;fontSize=9;fontColor=#333333;" value="&lt;b&gt;InteliSrcPA - PRD (Production) Environment&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;App ID: 22272 | Owner: Fernando Hidalgo&lt;br&gt;Naming: eec-aws-us-eits-intelisrcpa-prd&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scheduling:&lt;/b&gt; EC2 = 24/7 (Production)&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Encryption:&lt;/b&gt; All data at rest encrypted with KMS (auto-rotation, 30d deletion window)&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;RDS Config:&lt;/b&gt; SQL Server SE 15, force_ssl=1, MAXDOP=2, License-Included, TZ=SA Pacific, Enhanced Monitoring 60s, Multi-AZ&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;RDS Features:&lt;/b&gt; SSIS + SSRS (port 8443, 30% max memory) + Backup/Restore&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Patching:&lt;/b&gt; Windows (Crit+Sec+Updates) + Linux RHEL 8 / Ubuntu 22.04 (Crit+Important)&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;AD Integration:&lt;/b&gt; Self-managed AD (ena.us.experian.local) via Secrets Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Storage:&lt;/b&gt; Amazon FSx for Windows (Single-AZ 1) - DFS Namespaces + DFS-R&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;DR Strategy:&lt;/b&gt; DFS-R from FSx (AWS) to Windows File Server in DR Datacenter (Alterno) via VPN/DX" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="200" width="600" x="650" y="1700" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="color-legend" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;fontSize=9;fontColor=#333333;" value="&lt;b&gt;Connection Legend:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#ED7100&quot;&gt;━━&lt;/font&gt; Compute traffic (ALB/users/Jenkins to EC2)&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#C925D1&quot;&gt;━━&lt;/font&gt; Database connections (TCP 1433)&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#3F8624&quot;&gt;━━&lt;/font&gt; Storage (RDS to S3, EC2 to FSx SMB/DFS)&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#DD344C&quot;&gt;- - -&lt;/font&gt; Security (Secrets/KMS/AD)&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#E7157B&quot;&gt;━━&lt;/font&gt; Operations (Backup alerts to SNS)&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#8C4FFF&quot;&gt;- - -&lt;/font&gt; DFS-R / VPN / Direct Connect (DR)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#3F8624&quot;&gt;- - -&lt;/font&gt; AWS Backup target (tag-based selection)" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="150" width="300" x="650" y="1910" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="notes-dfs" parent="1" style="text;html=1;strokeColor=#147EBA;fillColor=#E6F2FF;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;fontSize=9;fontColor=#333333;rounded=1;arcSize=5;spacingLeft=5;spacingTop=3;" value="&lt;b&gt;DFS / FSx / DR Architecture:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1. Amazon FSx for Windows &lt;b&gt;Single-AZ 1&lt;/b&gt; soporta DFS-R.&lt;br&gt;   (Multi-AZ y Single-AZ 2 NO lo soportan)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;2. FSx reemplaza el File Server del DC principal.&lt;br&gt;   El DC alterno mantiene su rol de DFS-R target (DR).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;3. Operaciones gestiona DFS-R desde la misma consola&lt;br&gt;   DFS Management que ya conocen (transparente).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;4. EC2 Windows acceden a FSx via SMB/DFS Namespaces.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;5. Puertos requeridos FSx &amp;lt;-&amp;gt; DC Alterno:&lt;br&gt;   SMB(445), RPC(135), DFS-R(5722), RPC dinamico.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ref: docs.aws.amazon.com/fsx/latest/WindowsGuide/dfs-r.html" vertex="1">
